## OPENING PRAYER

IM: (_If a Chaplain is present—_) Companion Chaplain. |
    (_Chap. steps forward to the altar._)
IMor: _
Chap: Companions, bow your heads.

Note: I._M. uncovers head, and all Companions assume
  Position of Reverence.

>>> May the Supreme Grand Master graciously preside over
    all our councils, and direct us in all such things as
    he will be pleased to approve and bless. May our
    profession as Masons be the rule of our conduct as men.
    May our secret retreat ever continue to be the resort of
    the just and the merciful, the seat of the moral virtues,
    and the home of the select. Amen. {{endnote-ref sm-divine-pronouns}}

Response: So mote it be. (_Chaplain, if present, takes two steps
  back, returning to his line._)
IM: Companions, resume your stations.

%PAGE
%SPACE

## RESUMING STATIONS

Note: All return to stations. Music may accompany this
   procession, or Psalm 87 may be recited or sung: ||
   {{endnote-ref psalm-87}}

%SPACE
%COLUMN 0.7in 0
His foundation is in the holy mountains.

The [[smallcaps]]Lord[[/smallcaps]] loveth the gates of Zion ||
________ more than all the dwellings of Jacob. ||
Glorious things are spoken of thee, ||
________ O city of God. Selah.

I will make mention of Rahab and Babylon ||
________ ________ to them that know me; ||
________ behold Philistia and Tyre, with Ethiopia; ||
________ this man was born there.

And of Zion it shall be said, ||
________ This and that man was born in her; ||
________ and the highest himself shall establish her. ||
The [[smallcaps]]Lord[[/smallcaps]] shall count when he writeth up the people, ||
________ that this man was born there. Selah.

As well the singers ||
________ as the players on instruments shall be there ||
________ all my springs are in thee.
%COLUMN OFF

%SPACE 2

## DECLARATION & ATTENDING THE ALTAR

IM: In the name of God and our Three Ancient Grand
  Masters, I declare {{blank 6em}} Council No. {{blank 2em}},
  Cryptic Masons opened on the Select Master Degree
  in form. (_I._M. recovers._) Companion Conductor of the
  Council, display the Great Lights.

Note: C._C. advances to altar, squaring corners, opens the
  Volume of the Sacred Law to Exodus 16:32–35,
  places the Square and Compasses on the right hand
  page, and salutes the I._M. as a S._M., and returns.

%PAGE

%SPACE
## INFORMING THE SENTINEL

IM: Companion Captain of the Guard, inform the Sentinel.
CG: Companion Steward, inform the Sentinel.

Note: Without saluting, the Steward goes to the door |
  and gives ●●● ●●● ●●● to call up the Sentinel. |
  The Sentinel acknowledges by returning the same |
  ●●● ●●● ●●●.

Stew: (_Opens door._) Companion Sentinel, this Council is
  opened on the Select Master Degree in form.

Note: Steward closes the door and seals it with ●. Sentinel
  acknowledges by returning the same ●.

Stew: (_Faces C._G. & salutes as a S._M._) Companion Captain
   of the Guard, your order has been obeyed.
CG: (_Salutes I._M. as a S._M._) Illustrious Master, your order
   has been obeyed.

## FLAG CEREMONY

Note: This flag ceremony shall be given the first time the
   Council is opened for a meeting. After opening and
   before the craft has been seated, the Illustrious |
   Master shall remove his hat and say:

IM: Companions, salute the Flag of our Country, emblem of
   liberty, equality, and fraternity, principles worthy the
   devotion of every Mason.

Note: At the command "salute" all give the civilian salute
  of right hand over heart, facing the flag. The I._M. |
  may continue and proceed to lead the craft in the
  Pledge of Allegiance.

IM: ●

